* Overall results for top N finishers by sex (RaceRoster append).
*
* Purpose:          Lists the top N overall finishers for a specific sex category
*                   and appends the section to the Race Roster upload file.
*                   Used by @awards2RR.6.R.lst after RaceRosterHeader.rsm creates
*                   ~awards-5k.txt; each call adds another block of plain text
*                   (overall male/female headers and finisher lines) to that file.
*
* IMPORTANT:        Uses Destination Append — NOT plain Destination.
*                   Plain Destination would overwrite the file and destroy all
*                   sections written by RaceRosterHeader.rsm and prior calls.
*                   RaceRosterHeader.rsm MUST have run first — it registers the
*                   upload gate (External Report To + ##NNN##). Without it, this
*                   section writes to disk but is never uploaded.
*
*                   Does NOT repeat External Report To, Output Format, or the
*                   ##NNN## marker — only Destination Append is needed here.
*
* Param 1 (%1):     Number of results to display (e.g., 3 for top 3).
* Param 2 (%2):     Sex label for the header (FEMALE or MALE).
* Param 3 (%3):     Sex code for selection (F or M).
* Param 4 (%4):     Destination filename (must start with ~, e.g. ~awards-5k.txt).
*                   Must match the filename passed to RaceRosterHeader.rsm.
*
* Example:          OVERALL-RR.RSM 3 FEMALE F "~awards-5k.txt"
*
* See also:         Working example: C:\RunScore\SampleRaces\5k
*
Destination Append  %4
no page numbers
no column headers
Header
.ce ********** %2 OVERALL RESULTS FOR 5K RACE ***********
.End of Header
Field               Name
Field               AGE
Field               CITY
Field Length        15
Field               STATE
Field               CLUB
Select              SEX
=                   %3
records/page        %1
event               %awards_event%
